test.doc: This test case validates the SUT works correctly with single digit which has value type that is Hex string. - HH will stop reading digit label after reading exit numeric label and reject next digit labels if it is scanned. - If a number of digit label were scanned equaled value size of function then HH also rejects next digit label
test.status:
Several failures occurred:
1) Reading label: Code128_A Observed: Expected: A != True
2) Reading label: Code128_A Observed: Expected: A != True
3) Reading label: Code128_AB Observed: Expected: AB != True
4) Reading label: Code128_ABC Observed: Expected: ABC != True
